[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926749&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926749&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

Some questions on the initial cache data I should use for our
nameserver(s).

I) Our initial connection is via MILNET, shouldn't the MILNET address
   of NIC.SRI.COM be specified in the cache?

II) AOS.BRL.MIL has a third address listed in hosts.txt, shouldn't
   this address also be included in the cache.

III) Is there any reason not to specify the host names with their
    Domain address instead of their .ARPA addresses?

Following is a revised version of the initial cache data as I think
it should read.

Jeff
----------
;
;       Initial cache data for root domain servers
;

..               99999999        IN      NS      C.ISI.EDU.
.               99999999        IN      NS      C.ISI.EDU.
                99999999        IN      NS      A.ISI.EDU.
                99999999        IN      NS      AOS.BRL.MIL.
                99999999        IN      NS      NIC.SRI.COM.
;       Prep the cache (hotwire the addresses)
NIC.SRI.COM.    99999999        IN      A       26.0.0.73
NIC.SRI.COM.    99999999        IN      A       10.0.0.51
A.ISI.EDU.      99999999        IN      A       26.3.0.103
C.ISI.EDU.      99999999        IN      A       10.0.0.52
AOS.BRL.MIL.    99999999        IN      A       128.20.1.2
AOS.BRL.MIL.    99999999        IN      A       192.5.22.82
AOS.BRL.MIL.    99999999        IN      A       192.5.25.82

